## Steps to reproduce the issue

- build libysos statically
  - For now the only way to do it is using eg CMake (https://github.com/Interstellar-Network/yosys/tree/interstellar/cmake is a starting point cf https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys/issues/3239)
- run a basic workflow eg
```
Yosys::RTLIL::Design yosys_design;

Yosys::Pass::call(&yosys_design, "input.v");
Yosys::Pass::call(&yosys_design, "techmap");
```

## Expected behavior

libyosys should work fine

## Actual behavior

`No such command: read_verilog`
`33% tests passed, 4 tests failed out of 6`

## Temporary workaround

Linking with `-Wl,--whole-archive libyosys -Wl,--no-whole-archive` works but it is not ideal:
- it probably makes the whole linking/exe bigger
- in the Rust ecosystem we can not use `whole-archive`

`100% tests passed, 0 tests failed out of 6`

## Details

Basically because you are "self registering" with this:
```
struct TechmapPass : public Pass {
	TechmapPass() : Pass("techmap", "generic technology mapper") { }
	void help() override
	{
		//   |---v---|---v---|---v---|---v---|---v---|---v---|---v---|---v---|---v---|---v---|
		log("\n");
		log("    techmap [-map filename] [selection]\n");
		//...
		log("\n");
	}
	void execute(std::vector<std::string> args, RTLIL::Design *design) override
	{
		log_header(design, "Executing TECHMAP pass (map to technology primitives).\n");
		log_push();

		//...

		log_pop();
	}
} TechmapPass;
```

equivalent to:
`struct TechmapPass : public Pass {//...`
`TechmapPass TechmapPass;`

When it should be 
`struct TechmapPass : public Pass {//...`
`static const TechmapPass TechmapPass_;`
cf https://godbolt.org/z/Kve6jWx4M
NOTE: I am **not** sure that is enough, but it is probably a step in the right direction

The current version works in SHARED lib b/c the symbols(ie the *Pass globals) are kept around.
But in STATIC lib as those are not used, they are optimized out.

See https://gist.github.com/alexandervanrenen/c09af12a075a53eba9b6a07d992ed8db and https://gist.github.com/alexandervanrenen/c09af12a075a53eba9b6a07d992ed8db and https://www.cppstories.com/2018/02/factory-selfregister/

